RIYADH: The King Salman Humanitarian Aid and Relief Center (KSRelief) signed a cooperation agreement with the Sudanese Ministry of Health to refurbish kidney dialysis centers in Sudan, which will benefit 3,960 individuals. The agreement aims to support government hospitals with 18 kidney dialysis machines, 18 chairs for dialysis patients and five electricity generators. KSRelief also signed deals with organizations that will help hundreds of orphans and provide clean drinking water for tens of thousands of people. Elsewhere, KSRelief distributed 700 food parcels in Kabul, Afghanistan, benefiting 4,200 people. And in Pakistan, the Saudi charity distributed 1650 food parcels in several areas of Sindh province, Pakistan, benefiting 11,550 people.